benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/customFields/search/{searchKey} - Search custom fields

covered: Valid Request: Happy-path retrieval and variations with audit, Unicode, and default/no extra params are exercised (e.g., TC01, TC03–TC05, TC22, TC27, TC29).
Empty Response: Explicitly covered for no matches and offset beyond range (TC06, TC09).
Pagination: Limit/offset paging across pages and boundaries validated, including combination with audit (TC02, TC07–TC09, TC28, TC29).
Query Parameters: Broad coverage of valid/invalid inputs and edges for limit/offset/audit; unsupported params ignored; special chars, whitespace, very long keys tested (TC10–TC14, TC18, TC25, TC26).
Authorization: Missing and invalid auth tokens return 401 (TC15, TC16).
Error Handling: Malformed/negative params return 400; backend unavailable 503; wrong HTTP method 405 (TC11–TC14, TC17, TC30).
Non-functional checks: Concurrency and basic performance under load (TC19, TC20).
gaps: Rate Limiting: No scenarios verifying throttling behavior (e.g., 429) or rate limit headers.
Caching Behavior: No validation of ETag/Last-Modified, Cache-Control, or conditional requests (If-None-Match/If-Modified-Since).
Content-Type/Produces: No assertions that responses have Content-Type: application/json and correct charset; no Accept header negotiation or 406 behavior.
Default audit behavior: When audit is omitted, tests do not assert that audit info is excluded (default NONE).
Schema validation: No checks that each CustomField object conforms to the defined schema (#/definitions/CustomField) including required fields and types.
Ordering consistency: Pagination scenarios do not assert deterministic ordering across pages (e.g., stable sort by id/createdDate).

Path parameter formatting/encoding: URLs in steps include literal quotes around searchKey (e.g., /search/"email"), which is not a valid path; no test for proper URL encoding of special/unicode characters.
Authorization depth: No 403/permission scenarios (e.g., authenticated but not authorized) if applicable to this API.
Parameter bounds: No defined max for limit is validated; behavior for excessively large limit (cap vs 400) not covered; no overflow/very large offset boundary tests.
Case sensitivity: No tests for case-insensitive search behavior or audit enum case handling (e.g., audit=full).
recommendations: Add rate limiting tests: burst requests leading to 429 with Retry-After and X-RateLimit-* headers; verify normal behavior below thresholds.
Add caching tests: verify Cache-Control/ETag headers on 200; send If-None-Match to get 304; ensure bodies omitted on 304.
Assert headers: check Content-Type: application/json; add Accept header tests, including unsupported media type leading to 406 (if enforced).
Verify default audit: enhance TC01 or add a new scenario to assert audit info is absent when audit param is not provided (default NONE).
Add JSON schema validation of CustomField objects against #/definitions/CustomField (required fields, data types).
Add ordering test: verify consistent sort across pages and no duplication/omission when paginating.
Fix URL formatting in steps: remove quotes from path parameters (use /search/email) and add scenarios for percent-encoded searchKey (e.g., spaces, unicode).
Extend auth scenarios: if authorization is role/tenant-based, add 403 Forbidden for authenticated but unauthorized user.
Test parameter upper bounds and overflow: very large limit/offset; define and assert behavior (reject with 400 or cap to max).
Add case-sensitivity tests: searchKey case-insensitivity expectations and audit enum case handling (accept uppercase only or normalize).
